{
  "stem": "26609.8",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Prison was a different story, how I got to prison and what happened.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I told you, but I don't think it was recorded.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because what I said, it's when I came to Germany, but that was much earlier.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, they were different.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were entirely different.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A lot of changes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We thought that the worst is when the Russians, the Communists, came.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And because the Germans advanced from the west and we were in the east of Poland, so a lot of Jewish people, thousands of them, fled from the other side with the Germans before they came-- I mean, the Germans advanced and came to-- actually illegally, they came over to the Soviet-occupied part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They came to-- they stayed with relatives, or quite a number of them with relatives or hotels, motels, wherever they could, thousands of them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the Russians didn't want them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they surrounded every house at night time and got out by force those people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were called-- in Polish, they were called [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Not a special meaning, but because they fled from the other side here to our side.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were so-called safe, because we always-- we lived in Lwow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The other people came illegally, though the Russians surrounded house by house at night time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We could hear at night time screams, awful screams at night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't know why those people screamed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they took them by force to Russia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But they sent them far to Sibir, to Siberia, and to other places in Russia very far.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The children, some died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Others survived.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Not like in Germany, no one killed them, but from hunger or hard work.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
